            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> \"Just\" adding a depedency on setuptools is not a solution.\r\n\r\nYou mentioned that \r\n\r\n> Setuptools uses this distutils-precedence.pth \"trick\" to hijack sys.path. That only runs on startup if setuptools is installed as a system site-package.\r\n\r\n> It doesn't run if setuptools is located through PYTHONPATH.\r\n\r\nBut I did install setuptools with `pip` command and cythonize worked. Not sure if I understand where is the problem.\r\n\r\nNote: That said I am not *against* moving away from distutils but I want to understand if it is mandatory for enabling cython in python 3.12.",
